1
00:01:04,940 --> 00:01:05,940
Okay.

2
00:01:09,375 --> 00:01:10,751
Hey, besties!

3
00:01:10,928 --> 00:01:11,928
Wow,

4
00:01:12,346 --> 00:01:13,472
it's Monday again.

5
00:01:13,555 --> 00:01:14,932
It's a work day again.

6
00:01:16,183 --> 00:01:18,435
But before work stresses us out,

7
00:01:18,460 --> 00:01:20,503
let’s make ourselves
look good first.

8
00:01:20,729 --> 00:01:22,898
So get ready with me.

9
00:01:23,649 --> 00:01:24,858
Okay. Let's go.

10
00:01:26,110 --> 00:01:27,820
So, my first step every morning,

11
00:01:27,845 --> 00:01:32,458
is head to the bathroom to
shower with White Rose Papaya.

12
00:01:33,117 --> 00:01:34,881
There! Okay.

13
00:02:12,197 --> 00:02:14,867
Hey, welcome besties!

14
00:02:15,242 --> 00:02:16,326
Hi!

15
00:02:17,878 --> 00:02:20,876
I’ve been getting a lot of questions
from my Gen Z followers.

16
00:02:21,340 --> 00:02:24,027
Tin, what should we choose?

17
00:02:24,051 --> 00:02:25,051
Wait, wait, wait!

18
00:02:25,076 --> 00:02:28,084
So you’re thinking
about whether to choose,

19
00:02:28,356 --> 00:02:31,875
a stressful job with a high salary,

20
00:02:32,068 --> 00:02:34,570
or pursue your passion
where you are your own boss,

21
00:02:34,795 --> 00:02:36,255
but with no guarantee of stability.

22
00:02:36,280 --> 00:02:37,280
Hey!

23
00:02:37,700 --> 00:02:39,358
That's too much to ask!

24
00:02:39,900 --> 00:02:40,900
Wait.

25
00:02:40,993 --> 00:02:42,995
Uhm…

26
00:02:47,392 --> 00:02:49,853
Don’t you have any smart questions?

27
00:02:50,199 --> 00:02:51,199
Just kidding!

28
00:02:51,322 --> 00:02:52,407
That's hard!

29
00:02:53,241 --> 00:02:55,285
Well, I’m just -

30
00:02:56,703 --> 00:02:58,538
waiting for a sign too.

31
00:02:58,888 --> 00:03:00,515
Am I going to resign,

32
00:03:00,540 --> 00:03:01,583
or not?

33
00:03:05,378 --> 00:03:07,881
Oh, guys, I have to go.
I need to go to work.

34
00:03:09,632 --> 00:03:10,632
Sis!

35
00:03:11,134 --> 00:03:12,218
I have some good news.

36
00:03:13,828 --> 00:03:15,496
My pitch to the client got approved!

37
00:03:15,722 --> 00:03:17,515
I got a brand deal!

38
00:03:17,974 --> 00:03:19,559
Are you going to vlog again?

39
00:03:20,059 --> 00:03:21,603
Don’t you have a day job?

40
00:03:23,313 --> 00:03:25,064
That’s why I was thinking,

41
00:03:25,190 --> 00:03:27,942
what if I just focus on
creating content for now?

42
00:03:27,967 --> 00:03:29,944
What? You’re going to resign?

43
00:03:30,278 --> 00:03:31,529
You're overreacting.

44
00:03:31,905 --> 00:03:35,074
What about your share of
the rent here at the house?

45
00:03:35,450 --> 00:03:38,453
Tin, I still can’t afford
our expenses here.

46
00:03:38,536 --> 00:03:39,913
I’ll still help out,

47
00:03:40,012 --> 00:03:41,222
just not on a regular basis.

48
00:03:41,247 --> 00:03:42,247
Exactly.

49
00:03:42,248 --> 00:03:43,917
At least with your day job,

50
00:03:44,268 --> 00:03:45,894
you’re sure to get benefits.

51
00:03:45,919 --> 00:03:46,919
Benefits?

52
00:03:47,587 --> 00:03:48,922
What benefits?

53
00:03:49,255 --> 00:03:52,091
Don’t they know that with creating content,
you can actually earn more?

54
00:03:52,175 --> 00:03:54,052
You can earn more and even buy -

55
00:03:54,294 --> 00:03:58,256
life insurance, health insurance,
and make investments.

56
00:03:58,281 --> 00:04:00,867
I could even retire early
and enjoy life.

57
00:04:00,892 --> 00:04:03,019
And what I need right now is-

58
00:04:03,353 --> 00:04:04,771
peace of mind.

59
00:04:04,854 --> 00:04:06,272
Besides,

60
00:04:06,815 --> 00:04:08,650
I need to take care of my mental health.

61
00:04:08,733 --> 00:04:11,778
And also, I have an ultimate goal-

62
00:04:12,070 --> 00:04:16,125
to become a brand ambassador
for White Rose Papaya!

63
00:04:17,134 --> 00:04:18,802
That's why I always use it,

64
00:04:18,827 --> 00:04:20,745
so they will notice me.

65
00:04:21,037 --> 00:04:22,037
You know,

66
00:04:22,247 --> 00:04:25,542
if we ever get kicked out of this house
because we can’t pay rent,

67
00:04:25,708 --> 00:04:28,628
wishing you luck with that
“mental health” of yours.

68
00:04:28,795 --> 00:04:32,006
Also, don't put your stable job to waste.

69
00:04:32,423 --> 00:04:35,844
You’re a Junior Admin Assistant
at a glamorous fashion brand.

70
00:04:36,010 --> 00:04:37,136
Glamorous?

71
00:04:43,101 --> 00:04:44,602
Does this even look glamorous?

72
00:04:46,229 --> 00:04:47,229
Oopps!

73
00:04:47,856 --> 00:04:49,690
Oh! Olga...

74
00:04:50,275 --> 00:04:53,528
Here are the papers you had me
sign in the other building.

75
00:04:54,779 --> 00:04:57,797
What about the reports I
requested last Friday at 5 PM?

76
00:04:57,821 --> 00:04:58,821
Did you get them done?

77
00:04:59,909 --> 00:05:01,411
I’ll do it today.

78
00:05:01,578 --> 00:05:04,080
I don’t work on weekends
or after office hours.

79
00:05:04,163 --> 00:05:05,163
Oh.

80
00:05:05,915 --> 00:05:10,336
Oh, right. You have a work-life balance.

81
00:05:10,628 --> 00:05:12,297
What a shame.

82
00:05:12,463 --> 00:05:15,906
Our boss, who is the daughter
of the company owner,

83
00:05:16,222 --> 00:05:17,902
doesn’t get any rest.

84
00:05:17,927 --> 00:05:19,846
You're lucky.

85
00:05:22,849 --> 00:05:24,350
Speaking of…

86
00:05:24,893 --> 00:05:26,978
Boss is here!

87
00:05:32,775 --> 00:05:35,320
Madam, you look so fresh today!

88
00:05:35,486 --> 00:05:38,406
I hope you have a wonderful
and productive day.

89
00:05:38,656 --> 00:05:41,284
Is flattering part
of your job description?

90
00:05:41,326 --> 00:05:42,452
And showing off?

91
00:05:42,577 --> 00:05:43,745
No, Madam.

92
00:05:43,912 --> 00:05:45,163
I just initiated.

93
00:05:45,580 --> 00:05:46,706
Very good.

94
00:05:48,041 --> 00:05:49,918
So, what’s the plan for today?

95
00:05:51,377 --> 00:05:52,646
Madam, uhm...

96
00:05:52,670 --> 00:05:55,256
just a reminder that you have an
online meeting with your Dad.

97
00:05:56,132 --> 00:05:58,676
Maybe you should remind
yourself to calm down,

98
00:05:58,843 --> 00:06:01,137
and believe in the saying,

99
00:06:01,638 --> 00:06:04,641
“Keep calm and don’t overdo it.”

100
00:06:06,851 --> 00:06:09,437
So, what time is our meeting today?

101
00:06:09,604 --> 00:06:10,604
10:00 AM

102
00:06:11,314 --> 00:06:12,607
What time is it?

103
00:06:12,690 --> 00:06:13,775
It's already 10:30.

104
00:06:13,983 --> 00:06:16,085
What?! Why are you
only telling me now?!

105
00:06:16,110 --> 00:06:17,314
Make me some coffee.

106
00:06:17,338 --> 00:06:19,215
Go! Hurry up!

107
00:06:20,538 --> 00:06:22,040
These useless idiots!

108
00:06:22,851 --> 00:06:23,661
Jeez!

109
00:06:23,685 --> 00:06:24,811
Madam,

110
00:06:25,851 --> 00:06:27,645
here's your coffee.

111
00:06:28,020 --> 00:06:29,020
Okay.

112
00:06:29,045 --> 00:06:30,439
Be careful, it's hot.

113
00:06:31,190 --> 00:06:32,316
You may go.

114
00:06:32,775 --> 00:06:34,151
- Okay.
- Go, go, go.

115
00:06:34,485 --> 00:06:35,485
Okay.

116
00:06:40,074 --> 00:06:42,368
Lyda, the numbers don't lie.

117
00:06:42,993 --> 00:06:45,162
Your branch is losing money.

118
00:06:45,746 --> 00:06:49,166
Dad, maybe the people just
don’t have money to shop.

119
00:06:49,333 --> 00:06:53,379
Or maybe they just don’t have a budget
for our stylish clothing.

120
00:06:53,545 --> 00:06:57,383
And besides, they’re probably
just tacky, no sense of style.

121
00:06:57,508 --> 00:07:00,344
No, you’re not listening
to the young market.

122
00:07:00,594 --> 00:07:03,990
You need fresh and young ideas.

123
00:07:04,014 --> 00:07:06,451
Dad, I'm still young.

124
00:07:06,475 --> 00:07:08,811
Lyda, you're my youngest child,

125
00:07:09,191 --> 00:07:11,151
but you're not young anymore.

126
00:07:11,271 --> 00:07:12,958
You're what? Fifty?

127
00:07:12,982 --> 00:07:14,149
Dad,

128
00:07:14,858 --> 00:07:16,169
I'm only 45.

129
00:07:16,193 --> 00:07:18,070
Okay, I'm warning you.

130
00:07:18,654 --> 00:07:23,158
If you don't come up with a
solid new concept by Monday,

131
00:07:23,450 --> 00:07:24,910
I'm shutting down this branch.

132
00:07:25,244 --> 00:07:26,244
Huh?

133
00:07:26,269 --> 00:07:27,583
Shutting down?!

134
00:07:27,746 --> 00:07:28,746
Are you a choir or something?

135
00:07:28,998 --> 00:07:31,333
Why are you all speaking
at the same time?

136
00:07:31,375 --> 00:07:33,168
You’re really good, huh?

137
00:07:33,252 --> 00:07:36,046
Yes! We're shutting down!

138
00:07:36,213 --> 00:07:39,216
Unless we can convince Daddy,

139
00:07:39,425 --> 00:07:43,971
on Monday to let us present
something for the young market.

140
00:07:44,221 --> 00:07:46,932
So, guys, do you have any ideas?

141
00:07:47,057 --> 00:07:48,142
- Madam…
- Yes?

142
00:07:48,367 --> 00:07:51,662
Maybe we should try a new color palette.

143
00:07:51,687 --> 00:07:55,566
New? That’s the old palette!
You’re just recycling the same thing!

144
00:07:56,191 --> 00:07:59,546
Ma’am, what if we create
an online dance challenge?

145
00:07:59,570 --> 00:08:00,964
You’re really tacky, huh?

146
00:08:00,988 --> 00:08:02,716
Just as tacky as your outfit.

147
00:08:02,740 --> 00:08:04,366
Get out of here,

148
00:08:04,700 --> 00:08:05,700
use the restroom.

149
00:08:05,701 --> 00:08:06,910
How about you, Tin?

150
00:08:07,161 --> 00:08:09,556
Since you always have ideas, anyway.

151
00:08:09,580 --> 00:08:12,809
And you’re the one Daddy always
mentions as the young market expert.

152
00:08:12,833 --> 00:08:16,272
He keeps talking about you.
Alright then, what’s your idea?

153
00:08:16,692 --> 00:08:17,860
- Uhm…
- Well,

154
00:08:17,884 --> 00:08:18,945
think of something!

155
00:08:18,958 --> 00:08:20,394
Madam, what if…

156
00:08:20,418 --> 00:08:21,728
Tell me!

157
00:08:21,752 --> 00:08:23,313
What if we try something new?

158
00:08:23,337 --> 00:08:25,792
- Like a Style Swap Series?
- Like?

159
00:08:26,215 --> 00:08:30,487
Let’s collaborate with
Gen Z content creators,

160
00:08:30,511 --> 00:08:33,208
- who can swap outfits using our pieces.
- Really?

161
00:08:33,384 --> 00:08:34,950
It’s fun, relatable,

162
00:08:34,974 --> 00:08:37,458
- and it could even boost
our online sales, right?

163
00:08:37,483 --> 00:08:39,030
- What do you think?
- Just a “what if,” though.

164
00:08:41,017 --> 00:08:44,042
Why don’t you also look
for other new companies?!

165
00:08:44,646 --> 00:08:46,272
You sure have a lot to say, huh?

166
00:08:46,492 --> 00:08:48,995
Madam, you said I
should give a suggest—

167
00:08:49,020 --> 00:08:50,020
Eh!

168
00:08:50,118 --> 00:08:52,847
That’s a long suggestion you just gave.
Such a show-off.

169
00:08:52,871 --> 00:08:56,374
What are you proud of, huh?
That I’m older and you’re a Gen Z?

170
00:08:57,792 --> 00:08:59,729
Maybe we should just swap—

171
00:08:59,753 --> 00:09:01,063
You be the boss.

172
00:09:01,087 --> 00:09:02,773
You're such a bragger.

173
00:09:02,797 --> 00:09:03,797
Show off.

174
00:09:05,592 --> 00:09:08,190
If I were the boss,
I’d definitely be better than you.

175
00:09:08,590 --> 00:09:10,801
This is it!
I’m really going to resign!

176
00:09:12,489 --> 00:09:12,948
Why—

177
00:09:12,957 --> 00:09:16,044
Tin, just to remind you of the
reports I asked you to prepare.

178
00:09:16,069 --> 00:09:18,189
Print them and give it to Madam.

179
00:09:18,213 --> 00:09:19,565
I'll go down for a bit.

180
00:09:19,590 --> 00:09:20,590
Where are you going?

181
00:09:20,615 --> 00:09:21,615
In the lobby.

182
00:09:21,640 --> 00:09:24,184
My grandmother just arrived.
She came all the way from the province.

183
00:09:25,278 --> 00:09:27,030
What if Madam looks for you?

184
00:09:27,280 --> 00:09:30,534
You seem you're
not good at lying.

185
00:09:30,742 --> 00:09:32,744
Okay, I’ll just go downstairs.

186
00:09:38,208 --> 00:09:39,251
Okay.

187
00:09:40,127 --> 00:09:43,839
Madam, Olga sent this report for you.

188
00:09:44,089 --> 00:09:45,090
Where is she?

189
00:09:45,882 --> 00:09:47,342
She has something to attend to.

190
00:09:48,093 --> 00:09:49,136
What is this?

191
00:09:50,220 --> 00:09:52,013
Here, what is this?

192
00:09:52,431 --> 00:09:54,425
- Ma'am?
- "Outdated,

193
00:09:54,449 --> 00:09:59,038
but Ma’am Lyda
insists on keeping it.

194
00:09:59,062 --> 00:10:01,416
She doesn't like change.

195
00:10:01,440 --> 00:10:05,861
Old slide, but Ma’am Lyda
wants it there. You know,

196
00:10:05,886 --> 00:10:07,512
she's old."

197
00:10:08,905 --> 00:10:10,198
Is that old?

198
00:10:10,407 --> 00:10:12,075
I'm only 45!

199
00:10:16,037 --> 00:10:17,515
Olga!

200
00:10:17,539 --> 00:10:18,724
Don’t go in to see Madam yet!

201
00:10:18,748 --> 00:10:19,749
She’s angry!

202
00:10:20,083 --> 00:10:21,585
- Who is she angry at?
- You!

203
00:10:23,545 --> 00:10:25,839
I just stepped out for a moment.

204
00:10:26,173 --> 00:10:28,901
So, you go out during work hours?

205
00:10:28,925 --> 00:10:32,387
And you came back
without bringing anything?

206
00:10:33,471 --> 00:10:35,974
Actually. Madam has a point.

207
00:10:36,391 --> 00:10:40,187
Madam, I just went down
to see my grandmother.

208
00:10:40,395 --> 00:10:42,331
She just arrived from the province.

209
00:10:42,355 --> 00:10:44,959
It's a pity.
She’s been waiting downstairs for a while.

210
00:10:44,983 --> 00:10:46,359
You feel sorry for her?

211
00:10:48,320 --> 00:10:50,506
Well, you should’ve just gone
with your grandmother!

212
00:10:50,530 --> 00:10:52,657
Go back to your province,

213
00:10:52,866 --> 00:10:54,594
- because you’re fired!
- Madam?

214
00:10:54,618 --> 00:10:56,387
You even called me old,

215
00:10:56,411 --> 00:10:58,079
outdated? Here!

216
00:11:01,583 --> 00:11:04,294
Didn’t I tell you to check it
before submitting?

217
00:11:04,753 --> 00:11:05,753
Sorry.

218
00:11:06,546 --> 00:11:07,690
Madam, I’m sorry.

219
00:11:07,714 --> 00:11:10,568
Please give me another chance.
I’ll just delete it.

220
00:11:10,592 --> 00:11:13,511
- Just delete it.
- You have two choices. Pick one.

221
00:11:13,762 --> 00:11:16,932
A. The security guard will drag you out.

222
00:11:17,015 --> 00:11:20,119
Or B. I’ll drag you out
of the building myself.

223
00:11:20,143 --> 00:11:21,143
Uh…

224
00:11:22,187 --> 00:11:24,120
B! Come here, you troublemaker!

225
00:11:24,144 --> 00:11:25,690
- You're so slow to answer!
- Madam, no.

226
00:11:25,850 --> 00:11:27,646
Who looks older between us?

227
00:11:27,670 --> 00:11:28,920
- You actually look matured!
- Madam!

228
00:11:28,945 --> 00:11:29,999
- What are you waiting for?!
- Calm down, Madam!

229
00:11:30,023 --> 00:11:31,322
Get out of this building!

230
00:11:31,446 --> 00:11:32,980
And maybe get some Botox, too!

231
00:11:33,004 --> 00:11:34,714
Madam, I’m sorry.

232
00:11:35,090 --> 00:11:37,467
What are you doing to my grandchild?

233
00:11:37,931 --> 00:11:38,931
It's just her.

234
00:11:39,225 --> 00:11:41,787
- What do you think?
- You're bullying her!

235
00:11:41,811 --> 00:11:42,811
Correction:

236
00:11:42,836 --> 00:11:44,337
Insulting her!

237
00:11:44,785 --> 00:11:47,788
Why are they
insulting you, grandchild?

238
00:11:48,497 --> 00:11:51,416
Grandma, my boss
is just doing it for fun.

239
00:11:51,750 --> 00:11:53,961
She’s never experienced
being in a low position.

240
00:11:54,211 --> 00:11:55,855
- And this co-worker
of mine, - Me?

241
00:11:55,879 --> 00:11:58,590
has never learned to be responsible.

242
00:11:58,840 --> 00:12:00,926
She got me into trouble, Grandma.

243
00:12:02,010 --> 00:12:03,929
That’s too much judgment.

244
00:12:05,097 --> 00:12:08,183
Oh, she seems crazy.

245
00:12:10,560 --> 00:12:12,872
[gibberish chant]

246
00:12:12,896 --> 00:12:14,523
- Huh?
- [gibberish chant]

247
00:12:14,548 --> 00:12:16,125
- What's happening?
- Grandma?

248
00:12:16,316 --> 00:12:18,417
[gibberish chant]

249
00:12:22,531 --> 00:12:24,384
Grandma, what are you saying?

250
00:12:24,408 --> 00:12:26,535
- Is it a person?
- [gibberish chant]

251
00:12:26,743 --> 00:12:30,622
- Animal?
- [gibberish chant]

252
00:12:31,623 --> 00:12:33,500
[gibberish chant]

253
00:12:33,750 --> 00:12:34,793
Grandma!

254
00:12:35,294 --> 00:12:37,689
A place? In the Philippines
or other country?

255
00:12:37,713 --> 00:12:39,381
Madam?! Madam?!

256
00:12:40,841 --> 00:12:45,429
- Grandma!
- [gibberish chant]

257
00:12:45,762 --> 00:12:47,556
- Grandma!
- So, what?

258
00:12:47,910 --> 00:12:48,910
Is that it?

259
00:12:50,162 --> 00:12:51,162
Huh?

260
00:12:52,550 --> 00:12:56,637
Can we go now? Let's go back inside.
I have a different feeling about this.

261
00:12:57,013 --> 00:12:58,514
Get out!

262
00:12:58,806 --> 00:13:00,641
Where’s the guard?

263
00:13:01,017 --> 00:13:02,643
He’s being so lazy. Hey!

264
00:13:03,853 --> 00:13:05,646
Work, work, work!

265
00:13:05,896 --> 00:13:07,565
Back to work, guys!

266
00:13:08,941 --> 00:13:10,085
Ma'am!

267
00:13:10,109 --> 00:13:12,528
You, too! Do you want me
to pull your hair as well?

268
00:13:13,779 --> 00:13:16,991
Madam, were you scared earlier?

269
00:13:17,575 --> 00:13:20,161
Excuse me, I don't get scared easily.

270
00:13:20,828 --> 00:13:22,455
Me, too.

271
00:13:27,168 --> 00:13:28,669
Aaahhhh!

272
00:13:43,559 --> 00:13:44,602
Ouch!

273
00:13:46,687 --> 00:13:47,897
I feel dizzy.

274
00:13:48,189 --> 00:13:49,189
That hurts.

275
00:13:49,857 --> 00:13:50,857
What now?

276
00:13:50,941 --> 00:13:51,941
Were you scared?

277
00:13:52,360 --> 00:13:53,819
No, I wasn't.

278
00:13:54,862 --> 00:13:56,155
Me, too.

279
00:14:00,242 --> 00:14:01,369
Ahh!

280
00:14:01,494 --> 00:14:02,888
- What is it again?
- Shocks!

281
00:14:02,912 --> 00:14:03,912
Huh?

282
00:14:03,913 --> 00:14:07,500
Madam, they say the earthquake was strong.
It was a magnitude 5.

283
00:14:09,483 --> 00:14:10,483
Oh, so that’s why.

284
00:14:10,484 --> 00:14:13,921
No wonder the window was shaking earlier,
wobbling back and forth.

285
00:14:13,945 --> 00:14:15,614
That’s probably why I felt dizzy—

286
00:14:15,848 --> 00:14:19,702
because of the window… woah.

287
00:14:19,726 --> 00:14:21,083
It’s so dizzying, ouch.

288
00:14:24,940 --> 00:14:26,525
It hurts.

289
00:14:28,986 --> 00:14:29,986
Oh.

290
00:14:37,786 --> 00:14:38,829
Okay.

291
00:14:39,204 --> 00:14:42,833
So Tuesday, the product will be sent.

292
00:14:43,667 --> 00:14:46,753
Wednesday and Thursday,
shoot the content.

293
00:14:47,546 --> 00:14:51,175
Friday, Saturday, Sunday—editing.

294
00:14:51,383 --> 00:14:54,136
And Monday, submission.

295
00:14:54,595 --> 00:15:00,017
And of course, most importantly…
tomorrow, resignation!

296
00:15:09,318 --> 00:15:14,281
“Tin, please send to me
my schedule for tomorrow.

297
00:15:14,615 --> 00:15:15,615
Right now.

298
00:15:15,616 --> 00:15:16,825
Go, go, go.”

299
00:15:18,452 --> 00:15:21,663
Seriously, Madam?
It’s already late.

300
00:15:21,830 --> 00:15:24,124
You're unbelievable.
I’m going to get my beauty rest.

301
00:15:24,797 --> 00:15:27,858
Can we normalize boundaries? Thank you.

302
00:15:31,256 --> 00:15:32,591
Do whatever you want.

303
00:15:41,892 --> 00:15:42,994
Good evening, ma'am.

304
00:15:43,018 --> 00:15:44,417
My goodness.

305
00:15:44,520 --> 00:15:45,729
Good evening.

306
00:15:46,146 --> 00:15:49,584
Goodness, these Gen Z kids are so lazy!

307
00:15:49,608 --> 00:15:53,278
See? They won’t even do what I asked!
Gosh!

308
00:15:53,487 --> 00:15:54,964
Maybe I should just do everything myself.

309
00:15:54,988 --> 00:15:56,782
Ma’am, I’ll take your bag.

310
00:15:57,215 --> 00:15:58,310
You too, huh. Fine.

311
00:15:58,334 --> 00:16:01,005
I came up with the
idea, so I’ll just do it.

312
00:16:01,036 --> 00:16:04,206
I’m the boss, after all.

313
00:16:05,165 --> 00:16:08,835
I’m incredible.
I appreciate myself!

314
00:16:14,258 --> 00:16:57,759
[gibberish chant]

315
00:17:14,318 --> 00:17:18,780
Wow, I had such a good sleep.

316
00:17:19,281 --> 00:17:21,366
The bed is so comfy.

317
00:17:23,160 --> 00:17:24,160
Huh!

318
00:17:25,162 --> 00:17:27,623
Wait, what happened to my chest?

319
00:17:28,373 --> 00:17:29,499
Why is it so big?

320
00:17:30,792 --> 00:17:32,127
Oh no…

321
00:17:32,152 --> 00:17:33,152
Oh no…

322
00:17:33,712 --> 00:17:34,712
Ahhh!

323
00:17:36,089 --> 00:17:37,298
Overreacting.

324
00:17:37,609 --> 00:17:38,609
Wait.

325
00:17:39,875 --> 00:17:41,377
Ahhh!

326
00:17:42,329 --> 00:17:48,001
What's that sound?
It's so early. Stop!

327
00:17:51,400 --> 00:17:52,442
What's happening…

328
00:17:57,531 --> 00:17:58,531
Wait…

329
00:18:00,823 --> 00:18:02,158
where am I?

330
00:18:02,989 --> 00:18:05,533
Whose cheap bedroom is this?

331
00:18:06,162 --> 00:18:08,081
Why am I here?

332
00:18:12,710 --> 00:18:14,337
Oh, good, you’re awake.

333
00:18:14,587 --> 00:18:17,715
I’m leaving early, okay?
Hey, can I borrow your shoes?

334
00:18:18,132 --> 00:18:19,592
Who are you?

335
00:18:19,926 --> 00:18:21,886
Did you kidnap me?

336
00:18:22,595 --> 00:18:24,990
Don’t get ahead of me,
it’s so early.

337
00:18:25,014 --> 00:18:27,117
Come on, get up!
I’ve prepared breakfast for you.

338
00:18:27,142 --> 00:18:29,186
Your favorite: fried rice and dried fish.

339
00:18:29,727 --> 00:18:30,770
What?

340
00:18:31,062 --> 00:18:32,373
Fried rice?

341
00:18:32,397 --> 00:18:35,626
Really? You’re going to
feed me carbs this early?

342
00:18:35,650 --> 00:18:37,110
No, no, no.

343
00:18:37,318 --> 00:18:40,339
Hey, Tin! It’s way too early!
You’re so annoying!

344
00:18:40,363 --> 00:18:42,615
Alright, I’m going. Bye!

345
00:18:45,827 --> 00:18:46,827
Tin?

346
00:18:53,167 --> 00:18:54,167
Huh!

347
00:18:55,002 --> 00:18:56,002
Ugh!

348
00:18:56,754 --> 00:18:57,754
Ahhh!

349
00:19:00,007 --> 00:19:02,385
I'm really Tin.

350
00:19:02,719 --> 00:19:04,345
Thinner.

351
00:19:04,370 --> 00:19:05,580
Ahh!

352
00:19:20,528 --> 00:19:21,528
Tin!

353
00:19:22,155 --> 00:19:23,989
- Madam?!
- Tin!

354
00:19:24,510 --> 00:19:25,761
We’ve been switched!

355
00:19:25,992 --> 00:19:27,702
What are we going to do?

356
00:19:28,619 --> 00:19:29,619
Wait a minute,

357
00:19:30,079 --> 00:19:34,893
why is your outfit so colorful?
You look like a Christmas lantern! No!

358
00:19:34,917 --> 00:19:36,103
You're harsh.

359
00:19:36,127 --> 00:19:38,397
You, on the other hand,
look like you just came from a wake.

360
00:19:38,421 --> 00:19:41,083
Oh no, this will ruin my branding!

361
00:19:42,425 --> 00:19:43,819
What branding are you talking about?

362
00:19:43,843 --> 00:19:48,449
Let’s worry about getting back
into our own bodies first. Please?

363
00:19:48,473 --> 00:19:51,267
Exactly.
But how are we supposed to do it?

364
00:19:51,726 --> 00:19:55,396
Oh, do you still remember
what happened yesterday?

365
00:19:55,605 --> 00:19:56,605
Okay.

366
00:19:57,106 --> 00:19:58,232
Let me think.

367
00:20:00,777 --> 00:20:01,777
Ahhh!

368
00:20:02,737 --> 00:20:03,737
Oh!

369
00:20:03,780 --> 00:20:05,423
- There was an earthquake.
- Huh?

370
00:20:05,448 --> 00:20:06,966
- There was an earthquake!
- Yes, there was.

371
00:20:06,991 --> 00:20:07,991
And then...

372
00:20:08,618 --> 00:20:09,869
...then we collided!

373
00:20:10,036 --> 00:20:11,704
- Okay.
- What if…

374
00:20:13,770 --> 00:20:15,169
- Let's do it again!
- Let's do it again!

375
00:20:15,193 --> 00:20:17,153
- One, two, three!
- One, two, three!

376
00:20:18,753 --> 00:20:20,063
- That hurts!
- Ouch!

377
00:20:20,087 --> 00:20:22,298
It hurts. Wait, it's painful.

378
00:20:22,590 --> 00:20:25,569
Wow, so this is how it feels to be 50.

379
00:20:25,593 --> 00:20:27,220
- What?!
- My lower back hurts.

380
00:20:27,245 --> 00:20:29,364
Excuse me. I'm only 45!

381
00:20:29,388 --> 00:20:31,166
- Seriously?
- Yeah.

382
00:20:32,468 --> 00:20:34,535
If you say so.
One more time?

383
00:20:34,560 --> 00:20:35,978
- Again?
- Yes.

384
00:20:36,003 --> 00:20:37,498
- Ready?
- Okay. Ready.

385
00:20:37,522 --> 00:20:39,482
- One, two, three!
- two, three!

386
00:20:41,084 --> 00:20:42,084
Ouch!

387
00:20:42,116 --> 00:20:43,671
Wait, isn’t there another way?

388
00:20:43,695 --> 00:20:45,995
We might even have to go
to the hospital because of this.

389
00:20:46,781 --> 00:20:48,699
It hurts, ouch!

390
00:20:49,492 --> 00:20:51,077
Let's think of another way.

391
00:20:51,244 --> 00:20:52,244
What if...

392
00:20:52,453 --> 00:20:53,453
What?

393
00:20:53,830 --> 00:20:55,248
What if this is some kind of curse?

394
00:20:55,540 --> 00:20:56,540
Huh?

395
00:20:56,541 --> 00:21:02,088
Oh no! I don’t want
to be poor forever! No!

396
00:21:02,338 --> 00:21:04,549
You're overreacting about being poor.

397
00:21:04,632 --> 00:21:06,342
What kind of sorcery is that?

398
00:21:07,135 --> 00:21:08,261
You're so dramatic.

399
00:21:08,719 --> 00:21:10,054
Well, as I was saying,

400
00:21:10,638 --> 00:21:11,763
maybe this is a curse.

401
00:21:11,787 --> 00:21:15,540
A lot of people are jealous and
insecure around me, you know.

402
00:21:15,565 --> 00:21:16,566
You think they're jealous?

403
00:21:16,591 --> 00:21:17,634
- Yeah.
- Insecure?

404
00:21:17,787 --> 00:21:22,417
Maybe they’re just mad because
you actually have a bad attitude.

405
00:21:24,763 --> 00:21:26,056
Oops.

406
00:21:29,393 --> 00:21:31,186
I was about to get mad.

407
00:21:32,020 --> 00:21:33,313
But that’s true.

408
00:21:34,023 --> 00:21:38,454
So, I think you should
find me a witch doctor.

409
00:21:38,478 --> 00:21:39,664
Both of us should do it.

410
00:21:39,688 --> 00:21:41,625
Are you giving me orders?

411
00:21:42,316 --> 00:21:46,194
Why? Which one of us
looks like the boss right now?

412
00:21:49,907 --> 00:21:55,495
So no one will notice,
you do my work first,

413
00:21:55,787 --> 00:21:58,332
And I’ll be the boss!

414
00:21:59,124 --> 00:22:00,124
Yes!

415
00:22:02,847 --> 00:22:05,040
No, no, no!

416
00:22:05,339 --> 00:22:06,339
My gosh,

417
00:22:06,423 --> 00:22:08,625
my life sucks!

418
00:22:09,009 --> 00:22:10,427
- Good morning.
- Hi.

419
00:22:11,970 --> 00:22:14,056
It’s nice being the boss, isn’t it?

420
00:22:14,431 --> 00:22:16,558
No one’s getting in your way.

421
00:22:19,120 --> 00:22:20,120
- Good morning.
- Ahhh!

422
00:22:20,145 --> 00:22:21,396
Ouch!

423
00:22:21,605 --> 00:22:22,605
Aaah!

424
00:22:23,088 --> 00:22:26,101
I know you don’t care
about your dignity, but I do.

425
00:22:26,125 --> 00:22:27,269
- Get up!
- Ouch.

426
00:22:27,293 --> 00:22:28,544
It hurts.

427
00:22:29,587 --> 00:22:30,587
Gosh.

428
00:22:31,439 --> 00:22:33,190
Madam! Madam!

429
00:22:33,215 --> 00:22:38,679
You have three proposals, four revisions,
and five sponsors waiting for your reply.

430
00:22:38,929 --> 00:22:40,180
HR reports that our
burned-out employees,

431
00:22:40,180 --> 00:22:43,577
- are requesting mental health leave.
- Just say "I'll think about it."

432
00:22:43,602 --> 00:22:45,898
- If you don't know,
- There’s a discrepancy in the latest reports.

433
00:22:45,923 --> 00:22:47,415
- say "I'll think about it."
- What can you say about it, Madam?

434
00:22:47,521 --> 00:22:49,565
- I'll think about it.
- Madam?

435
00:22:51,442 --> 00:22:52,943
Tin, you’ve got a package.

436
00:22:53,360 --> 00:22:54,987
I’ll leave it here.

437
00:22:56,071 --> 00:22:57,071
Tin!

438
00:22:58,240 --> 00:23:00,200
Hey, Tin! Hey!

439
00:23:00,701 --> 00:23:01,744
Are you deaf?

440
00:23:01,952 --> 00:23:03,346
Who are you talking to?

441
00:23:03,370 --> 00:23:05,873
Of course, you. Aren't you Tin?

442
00:23:09,043 --> 00:23:11,563
Thank you!

443
00:23:11,587 --> 00:23:12,713
You're crazy.

444
00:23:14,548 --> 00:23:16,926
Once I get out of this body,

445
00:23:17,092 --> 00:23:19,094
I will fire you.

446
00:23:20,804 --> 00:23:22,306
But to be fair,

447
00:23:23,140 --> 00:23:25,559
he’s the only one
who bothered me all day.

448
00:23:25,893 --> 00:23:27,770
So this is what it feels like
when no one’s bugging you—

449
00:23:27,811 --> 00:23:29,646
- Where's your boss?
- Ahh!

450
00:23:30,231 --> 00:23:31,231
Dad?

451
00:23:31,607 --> 00:23:33,734
I mean, Sir…

452
00:23:33,984 --> 00:23:37,404
... she's in a long meeting.
Hold on, I'll call her.

453
00:23:37,655 --> 00:23:39,240
I can wait. It's okay.

454
00:23:41,158 --> 00:23:44,286
Uhm... Would you like me
to make you some coffee?

455
00:23:44,453 --> 00:23:45,453
Why not?

456
00:23:49,083 --> 00:23:51,603
- Madam’s in a good mood today.
- True.

457
00:23:51,627 --> 00:23:53,128
She's not yelling.

458
00:23:54,421 --> 00:23:56,924
She has a bad attitude, right?

459
00:23:58,092 --> 00:23:59,176
Bad?

460
00:23:59,885 --> 00:24:01,136
She's the worst.

461
00:24:01,387 --> 00:24:03,889
You know, she’s the leader of all evil.

462
00:24:04,306 --> 00:24:07,042
I think Madam isn't human,
she’s a monster.

463
00:24:07,518 --> 00:24:09,520
But no offense to monsters, okay?

464
00:24:13,691 --> 00:24:16,735
Oh my, it's true.
Isn't she a monster?

465
00:24:18,612 --> 00:24:20,781
You’re full of gossip.

466
00:24:21,448 --> 00:24:24,118
Why not do some work that
actually helps the company?

467
00:24:24,284 --> 00:24:25,284
Hey,

468
00:24:25,369 --> 00:24:27,913
you’re just Madam's assistant, right?

469
00:24:27,938 --> 00:24:29,398
So why the attitude?

470
00:24:29,832 --> 00:24:32,751
Maybe she wants a catfight.
You want to fight?

471
00:24:34,670 --> 00:24:35,671
Hey!

472
00:24:36,213 --> 00:24:38,674
Don’t get mad.
I’m only copying Madam.

473
00:24:38,799 --> 00:24:40,509
Her attitude is terrible,

474
00:24:41,635 --> 00:24:43,470
Like, garbage…

475
00:24:43,887 --> 00:24:45,723
No, a gutter.

476
00:24:45,931 --> 00:24:47,891
Oops, even worse...

477
00:24:48,058 --> 00:24:49,411
...like a septic tank.

478
00:24:49,435 --> 00:24:50,602
Septic tank!

479
00:24:52,521 --> 00:24:54,666
We're just only messing with you.

480
00:24:54,690 --> 00:24:56,191
So, do you want to join us for lunch?

481
00:24:58,110 --> 00:25:00,588
Sure, let's eat outside.

482
00:25:00,612 --> 00:25:01,612
My treat.

483
00:25:01,637 --> 00:25:03,425
- Oh.
- Good! Let's go!

484
00:25:03,449 --> 00:25:05,159
Go, go, go!

485
00:25:15,669 --> 00:25:17,230
Are you okay?
What's the problem?

486
00:25:17,254 --> 00:25:19,173
Oh, Ma'am there's a paper jam.

487
00:25:20,056 --> 00:25:21,408
Please don't fire me.

488
00:25:21,433 --> 00:25:24,097
Oh come on, you’re being
so dramatic about firing you.

489
00:25:24,121 --> 00:25:26,146
- I’ll handle it. I’ll do it—
- Madam!

490
00:25:28,514 --> 00:25:29,514
Oh!

491
00:25:30,099 --> 00:25:31,736
- Do your job properly, okay?
- Huh?

492
00:25:31,760 --> 00:25:34,103
Especially if you know nothing.

493
00:25:38,125 --> 00:25:39,125
There,

494
00:25:39,150 --> 00:25:40,735
she's back to normal.

495
00:25:42,667 --> 00:25:43,667
Hold on,

496
00:25:43,672 --> 00:25:46,258
I just need to calm my boss down.

497
00:25:47,833 --> 00:25:49,126
It was obvious.

498
00:25:50,127 --> 00:25:51,253
How was it?

499
00:25:51,278 --> 00:25:53,981
Did I pull off my dragon act?

500
00:25:54,005 --> 00:25:55,005
Hey!

501
00:25:55,841 --> 00:25:57,759
I don't get angry like that!

502
00:26:00,303 --> 00:26:02,139
Look at you, you're getting angry.

503
00:26:02,347 --> 00:26:04,450
Once this curse is gone,

504
00:26:04,474 --> 00:26:07,286
I’m seriously going to punch you!

505
00:26:07,310 --> 00:26:09,855
Look at you,
you're really angry!

506
00:26:13,733 --> 00:26:14,733
Fine!

507
00:26:15,610 --> 00:26:16,610
Alright then.

508
00:26:16,653 --> 00:26:18,822
I’m going out to eat with the two staff.

509
00:26:18,947 --> 00:26:20,699
They asked me to join.

510
00:26:20,866 --> 00:26:22,450
I’m tired of eating alone.

511
00:26:22,475 --> 00:26:23,726
Do you want to come with us?

512
00:26:25,287 --> 00:26:27,455
No. Thank you.

513
00:26:27,831 --> 00:26:32,478
I’m still going to practice
being the evil boss—

514
00:26:32,502 --> 00:26:34,958
I mean, evil spirit…

515
00:26:34,983 --> 00:26:36,276
That's enough!

516
00:26:38,133 --> 00:26:39,133
…of the glass.

517
00:26:44,268 --> 00:26:46,645
- It was amazing.
- It was delicious.

518
00:26:46,669 --> 00:26:49,440
- Thanks again, Tin.
- That's nothing.

519
00:26:49,613 --> 00:26:50,965
Love the treat.

520
00:26:50,989 --> 00:26:52,241
Let's do it again next time.

521
00:26:52,658 --> 00:26:54,476
Sure, treat me next time.

522
00:26:54,500 --> 00:26:55,626
Yes, of course.

523
00:27:01,408 --> 00:27:03,708
So that is how I look like when I’m alone.

524
00:27:04,281 --> 00:27:05,699
Pathetic.

525
00:27:09,829 --> 00:27:11,038
How are you?

526
00:27:11,413 --> 00:27:13,124
Why are you alone?

527
00:27:13,416 --> 00:27:14,416
Huh?

528
00:27:14,827 --> 00:27:16,120
What? Well,

529
00:27:16,245 --> 00:27:18,039
for a change.

530
00:27:18,247 --> 00:27:19,498
I'm taking some me time.

531
00:27:19,665 --> 00:27:21,459
I came by earlier,

532
00:27:21,667 --> 00:27:24,503
Your assistant told me
you had a meeting,

533
00:27:24,837 --> 00:27:28,424
and then she made me some coffee.

534
00:27:30,343 --> 00:27:31,469
Oh, right.

535
00:27:32,470 --> 00:27:36,033
Sorry about that.
Did she mess up? She's just new.

536
00:27:36,057 --> 00:27:37,057
No.

537
00:27:37,433 --> 00:27:38,433
It's okay.

538
00:27:38,476 --> 00:27:39,995
But actually,

539
00:27:40,019 --> 00:27:43,564
the way she made it, it reminded me
of the coffee you used to make for me,

540
00:27:43,731 --> 00:27:45,691
back when you were
just starting here.

541
00:27:46,442 --> 00:27:47,442
Starting?

542
00:27:47,443 --> 00:27:48,653
Yes, remember?

543
00:27:48,986 --> 00:27:51,405
You were once my assistant.

544
00:27:52,240 --> 00:27:54,116
But look at you now.

545
00:27:54,700 --> 00:27:59,014
But didn’t you just pass
your position on to me?

546
00:27:59,038 --> 00:28:01,582
No. You earned it, Lyda.

547
00:28:01,874 --> 00:28:04,061
You always say you're illegitimate,

548
00:28:04,085 --> 00:28:06,521
so you need to prove yourself.

549
00:28:06,545 --> 00:28:09,191
But you know what, you're my child.

550
00:28:09,215 --> 00:28:11,777
Unfortunately, when it comes to business,

551
00:28:11,801 --> 00:28:13,886
I need to make tough decisions.

552
00:28:14,303 --> 00:28:17,890
So, I'm looking forward
to your presentation on Monday.

553
00:28:18,099 --> 00:28:19,558
Or else...

554
00:28:20,851 --> 00:28:21,852
Okay.

555
00:28:22,312 --> 00:28:23,312
Sir.

556
00:28:23,337 --> 00:28:25,624
I mean, Dad.

557
00:28:25,648 --> 00:28:26,648
Thank you, Dad.

558
00:28:27,066 --> 00:28:28,317
See you on Monday.

559
00:28:36,409 --> 00:28:39,245
Okay, I'll eat now.

560
00:28:45,876 --> 00:28:46,877
Hello.

561
00:28:47,795 --> 00:28:49,297
You talked to Dad?

562
00:28:54,927 --> 00:28:55,927
Yes.

563
00:28:56,345 --> 00:28:57,345
I mean,

564
00:28:57,370 --> 00:29:01,517
He’s just reminding me
about our Monday presentation.

565
00:29:02,268 --> 00:29:03,268
Ohhh...

566
00:29:04,729 --> 00:29:05,729
By the way,

567
00:29:05,813 --> 00:29:08,065
- Yes?
- Before I forget,

568
00:29:09,108 --> 00:29:10,526
you got a package.

569
00:29:10,985 --> 00:29:12,570
What is that?

570
00:29:13,529 --> 00:29:14,840
My package?

571
00:29:14,864 --> 00:29:18,594
Oh, those are the Soleful Shoes...

572
00:29:18,618 --> 00:29:21,370
I need to create

573
00:29:21,871 --> 00:29:23,667
a content for my vlog.

574
00:29:23,706 --> 00:29:25,374
- Content?
- Yes!

575
00:29:25,708 --> 00:29:29,754
Because I got my
very first brand deal!

576
00:29:30,254 --> 00:29:34,633
Thanks to these shoes,
Soleful Shoes.

577
00:29:35,092 --> 00:29:40,723
But how am I going to do it?
This is not my body.

578
00:29:43,142 --> 00:29:45,478
Then we will wait.

579
00:29:45,770 --> 00:29:48,832
Let's just wait until
we’re back in our own bodies.

580
00:29:48,856 --> 00:29:50,191
Oh, I have an idea!

581
00:29:50,691 --> 00:29:52,669
Why don’t I just film you instead?

582
00:29:52,693 --> 00:29:53,693
What?

583
00:29:53,694 --> 00:29:58,050
You can just do the vlogging,
and I’ll film you.

584
00:29:58,074 --> 00:29:59,217
Is that okay?

585
00:29:59,241 --> 00:30:00,241
Please!

586
00:30:00,266 --> 00:30:01,410
I don't want to.

587
00:30:01,577 --> 00:30:02,577
Huh?

588
00:30:02,620 --> 00:30:03,871
Why don’t you want to?

589
00:30:04,121 --> 00:30:05,498
Don't push it.

590
00:30:05,664 --> 00:30:09,001
My final answer is no.

591
00:30:09,251 --> 00:30:10,896
- No?
- No.

592
00:30:10,920 --> 00:30:11,920
Fine.

593
00:30:11,945 --> 00:30:15,341
At our Monday presentation,

594
00:30:16,092 --> 00:30:18,844
I’ll just say "no", as well.

595
00:30:23,682 --> 00:30:24,826
Come on,

596
00:30:24,850 --> 00:30:26,875
you're so sensitive.

597
00:30:28,270 --> 00:30:31,041
- Alright, fine.
-But it's really a dream come true..

598
00:30:31,065 --> 00:30:33,251
I’ll help you.
How do we do this?

599
00:30:33,275 --> 00:30:34,985
Hello, besties!

600
00:30:35,319 --> 00:30:38,280
Welcome to my channel! Whoo!

601
00:30:39,108 --> 00:30:40,108
That’s how it is!

602
00:30:40,133 --> 00:30:41,759
Hello, besties!

603
00:30:41,784 --> 00:30:43,720
Welcome back to my channel!

604
00:30:43,744 --> 00:30:46,431
Oh no, Madam.
That’s not my branding.

605
00:30:46,455 --> 00:30:49,810
There’s no energy at all.
You have to go all out!

606
00:30:49,834 --> 00:30:51,419
- Okay.
- Yes.

607
00:30:51,444 --> 00:30:53,462
- One more?
- Yes! Repeat!

608
00:30:53,629 --> 00:30:54,755
From the top!

609
00:30:55,673 --> 00:30:58,568
Hello, besties! Whoo!

610
00:30:58,592 --> 00:31:00,487
Welcome back to my channel!

611
00:31:00,511 --> 00:31:03,431
- This is it! Whoooo!
- Yes!

612
00:31:03,931 --> 00:31:06,559
Not like that! Again!
From the top!

613
00:31:07,184 --> 00:31:08,601
Energy!

614
00:31:08,625 --> 00:31:09,996
Hello!

615
00:31:10,020 --> 00:31:13,023
Okay, and then say
"Step into my shoes!"

616
00:31:13,399 --> 00:31:15,443
Step into my shoes!

617
00:31:16,152 --> 00:31:18,612
Oh, adjust the angle a little bit more.

618
00:31:18,779 --> 00:31:20,423
- There, slowly.
- You're so demanding.

619
00:31:20,448 --> 00:31:22,884
-Yes, to make it really light on the…
-You sure have a lot of demands.

620
00:31:22,908 --> 00:31:24,827
So it will look comfortable.

621
00:31:25,369 --> 00:31:26,596
- What comfortable?
- Yes—

622
00:31:26,620 --> 00:31:29,391
I’m not comfortable without heels!

623
00:31:29,415 --> 00:31:30,415
Really?

624
00:31:30,542 --> 00:31:31,601
Yes!

625
00:31:31,625 --> 00:31:33,919
You can do it. Go, Madam!

626
00:31:34,503 --> 00:31:36,148
That’s okay now.

627
00:31:36,172 --> 00:31:37,750
There, good!

628
00:31:38,210 --> 00:31:39,210
Okay.

629
00:31:39,235 --> 00:31:43,572
Now, tell us why you
absolutely love Soleful Shoes.

630
00:31:43,596 --> 00:31:44,889
Well, I don't know.

631
00:31:45,181 --> 00:31:47,617
If it were up to me,
I wouldn’t wear this.

632
00:31:47,641 --> 00:31:50,770
That's harsh. But those are nice.

633
00:31:50,978 --> 00:31:57,526
Just tell everyone now how your experience
with Soleful Shoes has been.

634
00:31:58,068 --> 00:31:59,796
Which is?

635
00:31:59,820 --> 00:32:00,820
Ah.

636
00:32:01,822 --> 00:32:06,452
All right then.
You can just share my story and experience.

637
00:32:06,785 --> 00:32:09,872
When we were kids, we had nothing.

638
00:32:10,122 --> 00:32:15,419
So we went to school wearing just slippers.

639
00:32:16,045 --> 00:32:19,632
That’s why my Mom worked hard,

640
00:32:20,257 --> 00:32:24,345
so we could have proper shoes.
And these are the Soleful Shoes.

641
00:32:24,553 --> 00:32:28,140
You know, when I wear these shoes,

642
00:32:29,308 --> 00:32:31,644
it feels like my Mom is with me.

643
00:32:33,854 --> 00:32:35,231
Tin,

644
00:32:36,607 --> 00:32:39,777
I wish we could get back to our bodies.

645
00:32:41,278 --> 00:32:43,781
Because I feel like,

646
00:32:44,823 --> 00:32:48,077
you’re the only one who
can tell that story completely.

647
00:32:48,661 --> 00:32:51,121
Really? Thank you.

648
00:32:51,330 --> 00:32:54,917
Go ahead, keep going.
That’s good.

649
00:32:55,292 --> 00:32:57,729
Didn’t I say you should tell the story?

650
00:32:57,753 --> 00:33:01,215
Yes, but give it a try.
You’ve got this, Madam.

651
00:33:01,240 --> 00:33:02,908
I believe in you.

652
00:33:04,176 --> 00:33:05,219
Go ahead.

653
00:33:06,554 --> 00:33:08,305
There, thank you.

654
00:33:10,808 --> 00:33:11,808
Yummy.

655
00:33:12,643 --> 00:33:13,643
Tin...

656
00:33:13,811 --> 00:33:15,813
- Hello.
- Is Madam coming in?

657
00:33:16,188 --> 00:33:20,859
I’m here at the building
to pick up my things.

658
00:33:21,151 --> 00:33:22,194
Can you help me?

659
00:33:22,361 --> 00:33:24,071
In case they don’t let me in?

660
00:33:24,280 --> 00:33:26,657
This is not Tin. Idiot.

661
00:33:27,116 --> 00:33:28,659
What happened to you?

662
00:33:28,993 --> 00:33:30,744
Why do you look like
Madam possessed you?

663
00:33:30,869 --> 00:33:32,305
- I am her.
- And..

664
00:33:32,329 --> 00:33:33,932
And that’s Madam’s house.

665
00:33:33,956 --> 00:33:35,850
- Madam and I are together.
- What are you doing there?

666
00:33:35,874 --> 00:33:37,394
What do you need?

667
00:33:37,418 --> 00:33:39,336
I'm going to get my things.

668
00:33:39,503 --> 00:33:41,498
I’m going home to my
grandma's province—

669
00:33:41,522 --> 00:33:43,773
Oh, wait. Hello. Yes,

670
00:33:43,797 --> 00:33:45,360
is your grandma with you?

671
00:33:45,384 --> 00:33:46,552
Madam?

672
00:33:47,303 --> 00:33:48,321
Why do you ask?

673
00:33:48,345 --> 00:33:50,073
Your grandma cursed us.

674
00:33:50,097 --> 00:33:51,223
Cursed?

675
00:33:51,599 --> 00:33:56,601
- Yes.
- Yes, we've switched bodies!

676
00:33:56,625 --> 00:33:59,833
Oh! What my grandma said is true.

677
00:33:59,862 --> 00:34:01,781
I thought it was just a joke.

678
00:34:01,910 --> 00:34:02,910
Joke?!

679
00:34:03,115 --> 00:34:06,873
I have a presentation and my company
is at stake, and this is just a joke?!

680
00:34:06,897 --> 00:34:07,897
Exactly.

681
00:34:08,106 --> 00:34:11,210
I still have so many dreams —

682
00:34:11,234 --> 00:34:14,088
I have brand deals,
commercials, and so on.

683
00:34:14,112 --> 00:34:15,486
And most importantly,

684
00:34:15,510 --> 00:34:19,010
I don’t want to remain
in a body this old.

685
00:34:19,034 --> 00:34:20,136
Hey!

686
00:34:20,160 --> 00:34:21,745
I'm not old.

687
00:34:23,497 --> 00:34:24,497
Olga…

688
00:34:24,522 --> 00:34:26,005
- Please, Olga.
- I’m telling you,

689
00:34:26,029 --> 00:34:29,020
bring your grandma so
we can see what’s going on.

690
00:34:29,044 --> 00:34:33,340
- Yes, please.
- Oh no, Madam. She’s no longer available.

691
00:34:33,465 --> 00:34:35,842
My grandma passed away last night.

692
00:34:35,968 --> 00:34:37,612
- What?!
- No!

693
00:34:37,636 --> 00:34:40,990
- This can't be!
- Why now? Can’t it be rescheduled?

694
00:34:41,014 --> 00:34:44,452
Yes. And isn’t there an antidote?

695
00:34:44,482 --> 00:34:45,745
An antidote!

696
00:34:45,769 --> 00:34:46,996
- Please.
- No, there isn’t.

697
00:34:47,020 --> 00:34:50,959
But I know someone
who can help you.

698
00:34:52,025 --> 00:34:53,276
- Who?
- Who?

699
00:34:54,027 --> 00:34:56,530
I used to be a traditional
healer in the province.

700
00:34:56,555 --> 00:34:58,675
But I just shifted careers.

701
00:34:58,699 --> 00:35:01,118
Olga is my childhood friend,

702
00:35:01,243 --> 00:35:03,578
and I also know her grandma.

703
00:35:03,704 --> 00:35:05,038
That’s what she said.

704
00:35:05,455 --> 00:35:09,167
But how can we be sure
you’re not scamming us?

705
00:35:09,626 --> 00:35:11,938
If you don’t want to believe
me, you can just leave.

706
00:35:11,962 --> 00:35:12,962
Hey!

707
00:35:13,255 --> 00:35:14,589
This is our company—

708
00:35:15,648 --> 00:35:19,152
I mean, her dad’s company.

709
00:35:19,177 --> 00:35:21,847
You want me to send you away?

710
00:35:21,872 --> 00:35:22,872
Mhm.

711
00:35:24,349 --> 00:35:26,459
You’re so funny, Madam.

712
00:35:26,810 --> 00:35:29,167
I'm just kidding.

713
00:35:29,354 --> 00:35:31,273
You’re not someone
who jokes much.

714
00:35:32,232 --> 00:35:33,525
But it's not cheap.

715
00:35:35,777 --> 00:35:36,777
Fine.

716
00:35:37,362 --> 00:35:38,447
I can afford it.

717
00:35:38,613 --> 00:35:39,613
How much?

718
00:35:39,740 --> 00:35:41,742
And what can you do?

719
00:35:42,075 --> 00:35:48,266
For Package A, I’ll talk to grandma’s
spirit for ten thousand pesos.

720
00:35:48,290 --> 00:35:49,374
Ten thousand?

721
00:35:49,791 --> 00:35:52,687
What if she doesn’t talk to us?

722
00:35:52,711 --> 00:35:56,423
If she refuses to talk, that’s fine.
Let’s go with Package B—no problem.

723
00:35:56,631 --> 00:35:59,736
But the price is twenty thousand pesos,

724
00:35:59,760 --> 00:36:02,053
and she won’t have a choice here.

725
00:36:02,304 --> 00:36:07,184
I’ll let grandma’s
spirit possess my body,

726
00:36:07,726 --> 00:36:11,062
and she’ll be the one you talk to.

727
00:36:11,346 --> 00:36:13,908
Okay! Let's go!

728
00:36:13,940 --> 00:36:14,500
- Okay.
- Go?

729
00:36:14,524 --> 00:36:16,294
I’ll take the one where
she has no choice!

730
00:36:16,318 --> 00:36:17,628
Alright, I’m in too.

731
00:36:17,652 --> 00:36:18,652
Let’s go!

732
00:36:19,488 --> 00:36:22,091
Alright! Let’s hold hands first.

733
00:36:22,115 --> 00:36:23,760
- Did you wash your hands?
- Right.

734
00:36:23,784 --> 00:36:24,993
I used alcohol, don’t worry.

735
00:36:25,076 --> 00:36:26,429
- Let’s do this.
- Dont mind it.

736
00:36:26,453 --> 00:36:27,871
Fine.

737
00:36:28,163 --> 00:36:29,307
Close your eyes.

738
00:36:29,331 --> 00:36:30,457
- Okay.
- Yes.

739
00:36:31,041 --> 00:36:32,459
Is this it?

740
00:36:32,834 --> 00:36:34,377
What’s happening?

741
00:36:34,402 --> 00:36:35,402
Ahhh!

742
00:36:43,887 --> 00:36:45,138
What’s happening?

743
00:36:47,516 --> 00:36:48,850
What's with him?

744
00:36:49,601 --> 00:36:50,601
Is he okay?

745
00:36:52,896 --> 00:36:56,191
And why did you call me?

746
00:36:57,818 --> 00:36:59,653
My soul is already at rest.

747
00:37:01,613 --> 00:37:04,699
Oh! Wait, why did you slap him?

748
00:37:05,909 --> 00:37:08,078
So, there's an impact.

749
00:37:08,662 --> 00:37:10,497
Now, Grandma...

750
00:37:10,956 --> 00:37:13,917
Are you going to take back the curse,
or should I slap you?

751
00:37:14,084 --> 00:37:15,293
You have a terrible attitude!

752
00:37:16,753 --> 00:37:18,588
Hold on, Grandma,

753
00:37:18,713 --> 00:37:21,967
Please have mercy. I’m still young.

754
00:37:22,551 --> 00:37:24,928
I have so many dreams in life.

755
00:37:25,095 --> 00:37:26,972
Please help us!

756
00:37:27,806 --> 00:37:29,015
Begging doesn’t suit you!

757
00:37:29,040 --> 00:37:30,040
Huh?

758
00:37:30,065 --> 00:37:32,860
Is that so?

759
00:37:33,603 --> 00:37:35,373
You’re not going to help us, huh?

760
00:37:35,397 --> 00:37:37,403
I’ll kill you even if
you’re already dead!

761
00:37:37,427 --> 00:37:39,901
- Ouch! Alright, here it is!
- I’ll kill you!

762
00:37:39,926 --> 00:37:44,388
- Ouch! Fine! I’ll tell you!
- I'll kill you!

763
00:37:48,577 --> 00:37:49,786
It’s simple.

764
00:37:50,495 --> 00:37:53,248
If you want to switch back again,

765
00:37:53,415 --> 00:37:57,252
you just need to
change your bad attitude.

766
00:37:58,253 --> 00:37:59,253
Okay?

767
00:38:00,046 --> 00:38:01,046
That's it?

768
00:38:01,089 --> 00:38:02,691
- So cliché.
- Right?

769
00:38:02,716 --> 00:38:04,301
You’re old enough, anyway.

770
00:38:04,634 --> 00:38:05,927
It’s up to you now.

771
00:38:06,303 --> 00:38:07,429
I’m out!

772
00:38:08,179 --> 00:38:09,179
Ahhh!

773
00:38:10,265 --> 00:38:11,349
You'll get burned.

774
00:38:11,391 --> 00:38:12,391
What’s happening?

775
00:38:21,526 --> 00:38:24,988
Madam, being a boss is really hard.

776
00:38:25,363 --> 00:38:27,115
I used to think it was easy—

777
00:38:27,282 --> 00:38:29,743
just answer all their questions.

778
00:38:29,910 --> 00:38:32,621
But it’s not that simple.

779
00:38:33,705 --> 00:38:36,917
You have to decide on everything.

780
00:38:37,751 --> 00:38:41,504
And if you make a mistake,
all the blame falls on you.

781
00:38:42,631 --> 00:38:44,341
Your job is even harder—

782
00:38:45,717 --> 00:38:49,471
you’re constantly underestimated.
People look down on you,

783
00:38:49,711 --> 00:38:51,893
and you’re not even allowed to speak up.

784
00:38:51,917 --> 00:38:54,378
I think it's harder when...

785
00:38:55,212 --> 00:38:57,673
You have a higher role,

786
00:38:58,131 --> 00:39:02,042
yet people don’t respect you
and they look down on you.

787
00:39:04,072 --> 00:39:06,283
But think about it—

788
00:39:07,492 --> 00:39:09,667
if we hadn’t switched bodies,

789
00:39:10,913 --> 00:39:14,207
I wouldn’t have known
the employees here.

790
00:39:15,334 --> 00:39:17,461
Because of that,

791
00:39:18,128 --> 00:39:21,048
I learned their stories. Right?

792
00:39:21,256 --> 00:39:26,125
I should have become
friends with them earlier.

793
00:39:27,137 --> 00:39:31,558
Madam, it’s not too late yet, right?

794
00:39:35,187 --> 00:39:36,187
Unless,

795
00:39:36,772 --> 00:39:38,357
the company shuts down.

796
00:39:38,941 --> 00:39:42,027
That's why the presentation
on Monday has to be a success—

797
00:39:43,236 --> 00:39:44,905
not only for me,

798
00:39:46,239 --> 00:39:48,617
but for those who rely on me.

799
00:39:49,201 --> 00:39:52,287
- On us.
- Oh no, Madam! We need to make it work!

800
00:39:53,542 --> 00:39:56,712
Just 2 days left until Monday.

801
00:40:26,450 --> 00:40:28,410
Tin is so sweet.

802
00:40:31,413 --> 00:40:32,623
I’ll try it out.

803
00:40:41,247 --> 00:40:42,665
Hmmm.

804
00:40:48,546 --> 00:40:49,964
To be fair,

805
00:40:51,090 --> 00:40:52,090
it tastes good.

806
00:41:11,193 --> 00:41:12,193
Hmm.

807
00:41:14,447 --> 00:41:17,158
I think this is my new favorite.

808
00:41:19,744 --> 00:41:21,746
It’s fine even if it’s fattening.

809
00:41:26,813 --> 00:41:30,317
What if we try something new?
Like a Style Swap Series?

810
00:41:30,341 --> 00:41:34,213
Let’s collaborate with
Gen Z content creators,

811
00:41:34,237 --> 00:41:37,091
who can swap outfits using our pieces.

812
00:41:37,115 --> 00:41:39,093
It’s fun, relatable,

813
00:41:39,117 --> 00:41:42,162
and it could even boost our online
sales, right? Just a “what if,” though.

814
00:41:45,165 --> 00:41:46,708
She has a point.

815
00:41:48,602 --> 00:41:50,312
Check!

816
00:41:50,796 --> 00:41:51,796
Okay.

817
00:41:52,172 --> 00:41:53,172
Work wode.

818
00:41:53,840 --> 00:41:57,385
Madam, it’s the weekend
and we’re still in the office.

819
00:41:57,594 --> 00:41:59,179
Aren’t you going home yet?

820
00:42:01,056 --> 00:42:04,184
I'm just finalizing the deck for tomorrow.

821
00:42:06,645 --> 00:42:08,522
I wish I can do this,

822
00:42:08,980 --> 00:42:11,441
to make sure I really get it.

823
00:42:12,567 --> 00:42:14,277
Fine, I admit.

824
00:42:14,903 --> 00:42:16,321
I’m not young anymore.

825
00:42:16,488 --> 00:42:17,488
Come on,

826
00:42:18,115 --> 00:42:21,034
youth is just a mindset.

827
00:42:22,119 --> 00:42:24,704
Oh, by the way,

828
00:42:25,163 --> 00:42:27,809
your sister’s been texting a lot.
She wants to know where you are—

829
00:42:27,833 --> 00:42:29,876
I mean, where am I.

830
00:42:31,920 --> 00:42:34,965
That's okay. My sister is sweet.
She's also kind.

831
00:42:35,382 --> 00:42:39,112
She’s also asking when you’ll
be giving your contribution,

832
00:42:39,136 --> 00:42:40,833
for the house rent.

833
00:42:41,346 --> 00:42:43,640
But sometimes she can
be annoying too, right?

834
00:42:44,099 --> 00:42:45,099
Oh well,

835
00:42:45,600 --> 00:42:47,436
I’m not going home yet.

836
00:42:48,019 --> 00:42:49,437
I’ll stay with you,

837
00:42:50,438 --> 00:42:52,065
you won’t be alone anymore.

838
00:42:53,733 --> 00:42:54,733
Hold on,

839
00:42:55,235 --> 00:42:57,237
I’m just going to the restroom, okay?

840
00:42:57,362 --> 00:42:58,362
Okay.

841
00:42:59,322 --> 00:43:00,699
Faster, alright?

842
00:43:00,724 --> 00:43:01,724
Yes.

843
00:43:02,075 --> 00:43:03,075
Quickie.

844
00:43:03,201 --> 00:43:04,201
Quickie.

845
00:43:04,452 --> 00:43:06,204
What's this blue thing?

846
00:43:17,007 --> 00:43:19,634
Oh, you came home
when it was almost morning.

847
00:43:19,926 --> 00:43:21,761
I even thought you’d
be living at the office.

848
00:43:23,847 --> 00:43:26,016
There are just a lot of deadlines.

849
00:43:28,059 --> 00:43:29,436
By the way...

850
00:43:31,479 --> 00:43:33,857
Sister, here's the money.

851
00:43:36,234 --> 00:43:39,613
That covers one year of rent.

852
00:43:39,863 --> 00:43:43,116
So you won’t have
to worry about it.

853
00:43:43,450 --> 00:43:44,659
Where did this come from?

854
00:43:44,951 --> 00:43:46,161
This is a lot.

855
00:43:46,661 --> 00:43:48,598
From shady gigs.

856
00:43:48,622 --> 00:43:49,664
Really?

857
00:43:50,081 --> 00:43:51,583
I'm just kidding!

858
00:43:51,917 --> 00:43:54,000
That’s from my

859
00:43:54,169 --> 00:43:55,921
content creation gigs.

860
00:43:56,171 --> 00:43:57,339
I’ve been saving it.

861
00:43:57,464 --> 00:43:58,464
Are you sure?

862
00:43:58,506 --> 00:43:59,966
Wait,

863
00:44:00,425 --> 00:44:01,968
there’s something else
I need to ask.

864
00:44:02,552 --> 00:44:06,514
Sister, if I pursue
being a content creator,

865
00:44:06,765 --> 00:44:08,308
will you support me?

866
00:44:08,391 --> 00:44:09,976
Do you think I could stop you?

867
00:44:10,143 --> 00:44:15,023
I know you’ve been pressured
about the house expenses.

868
00:44:15,857 --> 00:44:20,904
But if doing content is what you
want to do, if it makes you happy,

869
00:44:21,446 --> 00:44:25,450
even if the income isn’t
stable, that doesn’t matter.

870
00:44:25,784 --> 00:44:27,160
What’s important is,

871
00:44:29,371 --> 00:44:30,914
knowing where you’re happy.

872
00:44:32,082 --> 00:44:33,082
Give me a hug!

873
00:44:34,251 --> 00:44:35,394
Is this for real?

874
00:44:35,418 --> 00:44:37,355
Yes! Come here!

875
00:44:37,379 --> 00:44:40,465
Thank you, sister! Oh...

876
00:44:40,799 --> 00:44:42,842
Go!

877
00:44:43,927 --> 00:44:45,220
Fight!

878
00:44:47,305 --> 00:44:50,392
What if we stop selling clothes?

879
00:44:51,059 --> 00:44:52,869
- What?
- Yeah.

880
00:44:52,893 --> 00:44:57,732
And then we make a
movement to the Gen Z.

881
00:44:57,941 --> 00:45:02,112
You know these Gen Z,
they don't really buy for trends.

882
00:45:02,529 --> 00:45:04,864
They buy for values.

883
00:45:04,990 --> 00:45:10,996
They care about creativity,
community, sustainability.

884
00:45:11,204 --> 00:45:12,580
So, what's the plan?

885
00:45:14,249 --> 00:45:19,045
The plan is we will launch the
new campaign, Style, Swap—

886
00:45:19,337 --> 00:45:20,982
and Slay!

887
00:45:21,006 --> 00:45:25,319
So, we will get Gen Z content creators.

888
00:45:25,875 --> 00:45:32,451
And how will you know if the style
suits you if you don’t try it, right?

889
00:45:32,475 --> 00:45:36,813
So now we’ll work with the Gen Zs,
collaborate with them,

890
00:45:36,980 --> 00:45:39,733
and then we’ll swap designs.

891
00:45:39,899 --> 00:45:44,505
They will design our
clothing pieces. Right?

892
00:45:44,529 --> 00:45:49,677
And the clients can get
credits for more discount.

893
00:45:49,701 --> 00:45:55,474
Plus, they can have their
old clothes redesigned by us.

894
00:45:55,498 --> 00:45:57,435
Or swap the style.

895
00:45:57,459 --> 00:46:00,920
So, let's go for this!

896
00:46:01,254 --> 00:46:04,049
That way, it’s sustainable.

897
00:46:04,382 --> 00:46:05,443
I like it.

898
00:46:05,467 --> 00:46:06,676
Really?

899
00:46:07,385 --> 00:46:10,055
I think now you understand
the young market.

900
00:46:11,181 --> 00:46:12,515
I'm proud of you, my daughter.

901
00:46:17,312 --> 00:46:18,646
Thank you, Dad.

902
00:46:25,612 --> 00:46:27,614
I'm proud of you also, Dad.

903
00:46:27,864 --> 00:46:29,008
Thank you. I'll go ahead.

904
00:46:29,032 --> 00:46:30,032
Okay.

905
00:46:30,116 --> 00:46:31,116
Thank you.

906
00:46:33,161 --> 00:46:35,121
Thank you.

907
00:46:37,165 --> 00:46:42,003
Let's Style-Swap-Slay.

908
00:46:42,212 --> 00:46:43,963
S-S-S.

909
00:46:44,506 --> 00:46:46,149
- Tin…
- Yes?

910
00:46:46,174 --> 00:46:47,985
You’re a great boss.

911
00:46:48,009 --> 00:46:49,511
Thank you.

912
00:46:49,969 --> 00:46:51,638
You listened to my idea…

913
00:46:51,971 --> 00:46:53,348
our idea.

914
00:46:55,266 --> 00:46:56,768
It’s nothing.

915
00:46:57,102 --> 00:46:58,520
I'm so happy.

916
00:46:59,771 --> 00:47:01,022
Thank you.

917
00:47:04,192 --> 00:47:05,985
Daddy likes it.

918
00:47:06,653 --> 00:47:08,798
- My daddy!
- Yes, your daddy!

919
00:47:08,822 --> 00:47:10,341
Yes! I'm so happy.

920
00:47:10,365 --> 00:47:13,451
What's happening?
I’m feeling dizzy again.

921
00:47:17,705 --> 00:47:18,706
Aaahhh!

922
00:47:32,220 --> 00:47:34,583
Madam, are you okay?

923
00:47:35,432 --> 00:47:36,242
- Ouch.
- Madam?

924
00:47:36,266 --> 00:47:41,938
I’m not sure if I’m alright.
My hips really hurt. Ouch.

925
00:47:43,982 --> 00:47:44,982
Ouch.

926
00:47:46,609 --> 00:47:47,609
Huh?!

927
00:47:56,953 --> 00:47:59,956
- Madam, we're back to normal!
- Yes!

928
00:48:02,709 --> 00:48:05,211
Yes!

929
00:48:06,254 --> 00:48:08,047
I miss myself.

930
00:48:08,465 --> 00:48:10,508
I miss my young body!

931
00:48:17,098 --> 00:48:18,933
Do you have a contact—

932
00:48:19,851 --> 00:48:21,895
Thank you... with Olga?

933
00:48:23,730 --> 00:48:26,441
Because I'm going to hire her again.

934
00:48:26,774 --> 00:48:27,774
Really, Ma’am?

935
00:48:28,067 --> 00:48:29,503
She’ll be so happy.

936
00:48:29,527 --> 00:48:30,958
Hold on, I’ll call her.

937
00:48:35,617 --> 00:48:37,367
- Hello?
- Hello, Olga?

938
00:48:37,368 --> 00:48:38,411
Yes, Tin?

939
00:48:38,703 --> 00:48:40,997
- Madam wants you back!
- Really?

940
00:48:41,039 --> 00:48:42,433
Yes, you don’t need to search
for a job anymore, alright?

941
00:48:42,457 --> 00:48:44,059
- Alright, I'll be there soon.
- Okay.

942
00:48:44,083 --> 00:48:45,126
See you.

943
00:48:46,711 --> 00:48:48,254
- Good.
- She'll go here, Madam.

944
00:48:49,130 --> 00:48:50,130
Oh goodness.

945
00:48:50,155 --> 00:48:53,259
Oh, Madam!
I also have good news for you.

946
00:48:53,384 --> 00:48:55,696
- Really?
- The brand deal has been approved.

947
00:48:55,720 --> 00:48:58,473
- Wow!
- They’ll be uploading the preview today.

948
00:48:58,723 --> 00:48:59,723
Really?

949
00:49:00,934 --> 00:49:09,625
Just imagine…
the swap really slayed opportunities!

950
00:49:10,026 --> 00:49:11,819
Wow, Madam, is that a new saying?

951
00:49:11,986 --> 00:49:13,238
Yes!

952
00:49:14,322 --> 00:49:17,367
I have something that belongs to you.

953
00:49:25,458 --> 00:49:26,543
Madam…

954
00:49:26,876 --> 00:49:29,546
You’re young, I get it.

955
00:49:29,754 --> 00:49:32,423
I know you have many
things you still want to do,

956
00:49:33,258 --> 00:49:35,134
and goals to achieve.

957
00:49:37,345 --> 00:49:40,056
I think I'll think about it first, Madam.

958
00:49:40,598 --> 00:49:41,641
That's my line.

959
00:49:44,602 --> 00:49:46,145
I learned it from you.

960
00:49:46,271 --> 00:49:47,271
Really?

961
00:49:47,605 --> 00:49:49,315
The truth is, Madam,

962
00:49:49,440 --> 00:49:51,359
I still want to learn.

963
00:49:52,068 --> 00:49:55,863
So for now,
I’ll stay here in this company.

964
00:49:56,239 --> 00:49:57,239
Really?

965
00:49:57,365 --> 00:49:59,867
Oh, thank you!

966
00:50:00,118 --> 00:50:03,955
Just remember, you’ll be your own boss—
you’ll be a great boss.

967
00:50:03,997 --> 00:50:06,416
Go! Push!

968
00:50:07,893 --> 00:50:08,893
Thank you.

969
00:50:08,918 --> 00:50:10,020
Thank you, madam.

970
00:50:10,044 --> 00:50:12,755
Yes, the best boss.

971
00:50:13,464 --> 00:50:15,174
Oh, someone's calling.

972
00:50:16,652 --> 00:50:17,652
Hello?

973
00:50:17,677 --> 00:50:19,667
Is this Tin, the content creator?

974
00:50:20,054 --> 00:50:21,347
Yes, speaking.

975
00:50:21,556 --> 00:50:22,575
Who is this?

976
00:50:22,599 --> 00:50:26,620
Hi, I'm Jennie,
brand manager of White Rose Papaya.

977
00:50:26,644 --> 00:50:29,081
We want to get you for
a brand collaboration.

978
00:50:29,105 --> 00:50:30,105
Are you up for it?

979
00:50:30,648 --> 00:50:32,108
Yes, Ma'am!

980
00:50:33,192 --> 00:50:34,444
Thank you!

981
00:50:35,437 --> 00:50:37,250
Madam, another good news!

982
00:50:37,275 --> 00:50:38,318
What is it?!

983
00:50:38,328 --> 00:50:39,412
White Rose Papaya!

984
00:50:39,437 --> 00:50:40,521
Ahhh!

985
00:50:41,957 --> 00:50:44,000
You see. Congratulations!

986
00:50:44,024 --> 00:50:45,024
Thank you, Madam.

987
00:50:45,335 --> 00:50:46,604
Push!

988
00:50:46,628 --> 00:50:48,046
- Go!
- Yeah!
